Yes, too right! We also ensure that students have a session at the end of each meeting with JUST the committee chair and external member (i.e. the two who are not supervisors) at which they can air any concerns in confidence.

It's been standard practice here (biomedsci in the UK) for as long as I can remember for thesis committees to be chaired by non-supervisors, and usually by senior experienced people. Supervisors are on the committee and can certainly influence things but not to this extent.
